### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
### AGENTIC FLOWS  — POST /agent
### Each test shows the expected planner steps in comments
### ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### ── 13. Agent: fetch specs + generate summary for Tesla
### Expected planner steps:
###   1. fetch_vehicle_specs  { vehicleId: "tesla-model3-2025-long-range" }
###   2. generate_vehicle_summary  { vehicleId: "tesla-model3-2025-long-range" }
###   3. stop
### Expected response: narrative summary paragraph about the Tesla
POST http://localhost:8080/agent
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "Give me a summary of the Tesla Model 3 Long Range",
  "docId": "tesla-model3-2025-long-range",
  "topK": 3
}

###

### ── 14. Agent: compare Tesla vs BMW
### Expected planner steps:
###   1. compare_vehicles { vehicleIds: "tesla-model3-2025-long-range,bmw-m3-2025-competition", question: "performance and value" }
###   2. stop
### Expected response: side-by-side comparison paragraph
POST http://localhost:8080/agent
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "Compare the Tesla Model 3 and BMW M3 on performance and value",
  "topK": 3
}

###

### ── 15. Agent: enrich vehicle summary
### Expected planner steps:
###   1. enrich_vehicle_data { vehicleId: "bmw-m3-2025-competition" }
###   2. stop
### Expected response: confirmation that vehicle was enriched and re-ingested
POST http://localhost:8080/agent
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "Enrich and improve the summary for the BMW M3 Competition",
  "docId": "bmw-m3-2025-competition",
  "topK": 1
}

###

### ── 16. Agent: fetch specs then email summary
### Expected planner steps:
###   1. fetch_vehicle_specs  { vehicleId: "tesla-model3-2025-long-range" }
###   2. generate_vehicle_summary  { vehicleId: "tesla-model3-2025-long-range" }
###   3. email  { recipient: "sales@dealership.com", subject: "Tesla Model 3 Summary" }
###   4. stop
POST http://localhost:8080/agent
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "Summarize the Tesla Model 3 Long Range and email the summary to sales@dealership.com",
  "docId": "tesla-model3-2025-long-range",
  "topK": 3,
  "recipientEmail": "sales@dealership.com"
}

###

### ── 17. Agent: plain research question (existing pipeline — not vehicle tools)
### Expected planner steps:
###   1. research  { query: "spring boot dependency injection" }
###   2. stop
### This verifies existing non-vehicle agent flow still works after your changes
POST http://localhost:8080/agent
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "prompt": "What is dependency injection in Spring Boot?",
  "docId": "spring-boot-qa",
  "topK": 5
}

###

